<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A rough model you could have for the crypto cr=
edit crisis of 2022 is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Everything was=C2=A0real, real ricket=
y.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">All of the big serious players =
could see that everything was rickety.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5=
px;">This created obvious economic opportunities: Pick a rickety thing, bet=
 on it collapsing, give it a gentle poke, watch it collapse=C2=A0and collec=
t your winnings.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">These opportuniti=
es were tempting: If you were a big serious player, you could see the oppor=
tunities, and you could sort of do the math on a napkin of how much money y=
ou=E2=80=99d make from a little poking.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: =
5px;">But=C2=A0<em>everything=C2=A0</em>was real, real rickety, including y=
ou. The big serious players in crypto were themselves opaque, levered, risk=
-loving and rickety.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you poked =
something else and it collapsed, that would undermine confidence in crypto =
generally, and the main thing keeping=C2=A0<em>your=C2=A0</em>project going=
 was confidence in crypto generally.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px=
;">Also the people whose project you poked might want revenge, so they migh=
t poke you back.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One way to put this is that big serious player=
s in crypto are long crypto volatility at a small scale, but short crypto v=
olatility at a large scale.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !importa=
nt; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0At the level of napkin math, you could say =E2=80=9Cif Thing X go=
es down, I will make $200 million, and I would like to make $200 million=E2=
=80=9D; more volatility means more trades. But at a more conceptual level, =
if Thing X goes down, that increases the chances that <em>you</em> will als=
o go down. If Thing X goes down by 50%, you make money. If Thing X goes dow=
n by 100%, you go bankrupt and become an international fugitive. You are lo=
ng a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29960075.2675=
30/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuaW52ZXN0b3BlZGlhLmNvbS90ZXJtcy9iL2JlYXJwdXRzcHJlYWQuYXNw=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4eebc241" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> put spread</a> I guess.=C2=A0<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another way to put this is=C2=A0that there was=
, in crypto, a=C2=A0sort of <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.=
com/click/29960075.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2Fyd=
GljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMDcvbW92aWVwYXNzLXdhcy1ub3QtYS1nb29kLWJ1c2luZXNzP2NtcGlk=
PUJCRDEyMTIyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV=
0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTIxMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB59b9d3a4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">  half-understood imperfect equilibrium</a> o=
f mutually assured destruction: If everyone joined together to generously p=
raise each other=E2=80=99s projects, they would bolster overall confidence =
in the crypto financial system, and all of their projects would attract inv=
estors and do well. If one person said =E2=80=9Cnah those other projects ar=
e frauds,=E2=80=9D the other projects would collapse, but so would that guy=
=E2=80=99s project. But nobody knew for sure exactly what the limits were, =
and there were temptations to cheat.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another way to put it is, like, =E2=80=9C(3, 3=
)=E2=80=9D? One <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29=
960075.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9mZWF0dXJlcy8yMDIyLXRoZS1jc=
nlwdG8tc3RvcnkvP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEyMTIyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwm=
dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTIxMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXl=
zdHVmZiNkZWZp/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB979aa018" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">amazing crypto pro=
ject</a>=C2=A0was (is, I guess) <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/29960075.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cub2x5bXB1c2Rhby5maW5hbmNlLw/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB26452540" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> OlympusDAO</a>, whose basic premi=
se was=C2=A0that if everyone bought its tokens and didn=E2=80=99t sell them=
, then everyone would make money =E2=80=94=C2=A0whereas if you sold the tok=
ens, you would lose money (because the tokens would go down as you sold the=
m) and so would everyone else. In the glory days, <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29960075.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGV4YW5kZXItcm9=
6bm93c2tpLm1lZGl1bS5jb20vdGhlLW9obWl6YXRpb24tb2YtZGVmaS0zLTMtOWU0MTA1MDllMG=
Fj/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB31ac0859" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Olympus enthusiasts</a>=C2=
=A0dressed up this insight in the notation=C2=A0of game theory:=C2=A0=E2=80=
=9C(3, 3)=E2=80=9D was their way of saying that if everyone buys it it will=
 go up, while =E2=80=9C(-3, -3)=E2=80=9D means that if everyone sells it it=
 will go down.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When I first found out about Olympus, and this=
 notation, and what it meant, I laughed really hard for a long time. What a=
 trivial point, I thought. But after the last few months I have developed a=
 certain respect for it. In a sense the game theory of crypto is obvious, b=
ut Olympus was right to=C2=A0<em>emphasize </em>it. This idea =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0=E2=80=9Cif everyone cooperates, we=E2=80=99ll all get richer, but if pe=
ople defect it will collapse=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0might be close to the =
core of crypto.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway the New York Times <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29960075.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW=
1lcy5jb20vMjAyMi8xMi8wNy9idXNpbmVzcy9mdHgtc2JmLWNyeXB0by1tYXJrZXQtaW52ZXN0a=
WdhdGlvbi5odG1sP3NtaWQ9bnl0Y29yZS1pb3Mtc2hhcmUmcmVmZXJyaW5nU291cmNlPWFydGlj=
bGVTaGFyZQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB94021bd0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> reported last week</=
a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Federal prosecutors are investigating whether =
FTX=E2=80=99s founder, Sam Bankman-Fried, manipulated the market for two cr=
yptocurrencies this past spring, leading to their collapse and creating a d=
omino effect that eventually caused the implosion of his own cryptocurrency=
 exchange last month, according to two people with knowledge of the matter.=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">U.S. prosecutors in Manhattan are examining th=
e possibility that Mr. Bankman-Fried steered the prices of two interlinked =
currencies, TerraUSD and Luna, to benefit the entities he controlled, inclu=
ding FTX and Alameda Research, a hedge fund he co-founded and owned, the pe=
ople said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The investigation is in its early stages, and =
it is not clear whether prosecutors have determined any wrongdoing by Mr. B=
ankman-Fried, or when they began looking at the TerraUSD and Luna trades. =
=E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In May, major cryptocurrency market makers =E2=
=80=94 exchanges or individuals who arrange for buyers and sellers to be ma=
tched =E2=80=94 noticed a flood of =E2=80=9Csell=E2=80=9D orders coming in =
for TerraUSD, said one person with knowledge of the market activity. The or=
ders were in small denominations, but they were placed very quickly, the pe=
rson said. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The exact causes of the collapse of the two cr=
yptocurrencies remain unclear. However, the bulk of the sell orders for Ter=
raUSD appeared to be coming from one place: Sam Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s cry=
ptocurrency trading firm, which also placed a big bet on the price of Luna =
falling, according to the person with knowledge of the market activity.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Had the trade gone as expected, the price decl=
ines in Luna could have yielded a fat profit. Instead, the bottom fell out =
of the entire TerraUSD-Luna ecosystem. The collapse caused more trouble in =
the cryptocurrency industry, sending several prominent companies into bankr=
uptcy and erasing about $1 trillion in value from the crypto market.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The ripple effects from the Luna crash ultimat=
ely contributed to the collapse of Mr. Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s business emp=
ire. In November, Caroline Ellison, the chief executive of Alameda, told st=
aff that loans to Alameda were recalled as a result of the market chaos unl=
eashed by the crash, according to a person familiar with the matter. But th=
e funds that Alameda had borrowed were no longer easily available, Ms. Elli=
son told the staff, so the company used FTX customer funds to make the paym=
ents.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One technical version of this story would be t=
hat Alameda was both a directional prop trading firm and a big market maker=
 on FTX. In its prop business, it (perhaps) had a big bet against Luna, whi=
ch made money as Luna went down. In its market-making business, it served a=
s a sort of buyer of last resort on FTX, and as people dumped Luna it ended=
 up buying their Luna. It could have been short Luna at the start of the co=
llapse but long Luna by the middle of the collapse, meaning that it lost a =
lot of money by the end of the collapse. It was long Luna volatility at a s=
mall scale, but short Luna volatility on a large scale. There is <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29960075.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTUvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmU=
tcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1iaW5hbmNlLWZ0eC1hbmQtY2Fycz9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMjEyMjJfTU9ORV=
lTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yM=
jEyMTImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa2c76fa6" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">  some speculation</a> that that=E2=80=99s=C2=A0what happened.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But a less technical version of the story woul=
d be that Alameda might have made or lost money on the Luna trade, but what=
 ultimately sunk Alameda and FTX was not how much money they made or lost o=
n any particular trades. What sunk them was some combination of (1) a gigan=
tic hole in their balance sheets, (2) an attempt to cover over that hole wi=
th <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29960075.267530=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTQvZn=
R4LXMtYmFsYW5jZS1zaGVldC13YXMtYmFkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEyMTIyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0b=
V9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTIxMiZ1dG1f=
Y2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB78530f11" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  a t=
hin layer of magic-bean tokens</a> that FTX had made up and that it ascribe=
d enormous value to, and (3) people noticing. If Luna had not collapsed, FT=
X=E2=80=99s magic-bean tokens might have held their value better, people mi=
ght not have noticed the problems, no one would have withdrawn their money =
and the whole thing could have kept going.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/29960075.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTItMDUvY3J5cHRvLWhhZC1hLWNyZWRpdC1idWJibGU_Y21waWQ9QkJE=
MTIxMjIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXI=
mdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIxMjEyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cBe67fe569" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">  talked last week</a> about Kyle Davies=E2=80=99s re=
vealing interview with Hugh Hendry about how Three Arrows Capital, or 3AC, =
collapsed. Davies and his co-founder Su Zhu ran 3AC, a prop trading firm mu=
ch like Alameda; they were long Luna and lost money on the collapse. <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29960075.267530/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vd2F0Y2g_dj10SmlRaUw1YkxZMA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
B0de2bc93" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;"> Part II of that interview</a> was posted on Friday, and=
 in it Davies says casually that 3AC was surprised by the Luna collapse, bu=
t lost only $200 million on it, not a huge hit compared to 3AC=E2=80=99s bi=
llions under management. Luna is not what blew up 3AC. But after the Luna c=
ollapse, confidence in crypto financial firms collapsed, and so lenders rec=
alled loans from firms like 3AC and Alameda. That is=C2=A0<em>also=C2=A0</e=
m>not what blew up 3AC, in Davies=E2=80=99s telling: 3AC had enough money t=
o repay its lenders. What blew up 3AC was the third-order effect: Lenders r=
ecalled loans from crypto hedge funds, and so all the popular crypto hedge =
fund trades collapsed as those funds were forced to sell; 3AC was in all th=
e popular crypto hedge fund trades and lost money on all of them, and <em>t=
hen </em>it ran out of money to pay its lenders. If 3AC had been=C2=A0<em>s=
hort </em>Luna, it might have made $200 million on that trade, but the $200=
 million would not have helped that much. The big problem was not any parti=
cular trade, but the collapse of the whole=C2=A0ecosystem in which everyone=
 was making money doing the same trades.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is a funny interview because Davies says =
=E2=80=9Cthere were numerous black swans that happened=C2=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=A0=
some of which were really quite extreme, I thought,=E2=80=9D and you can so=
rt of watch Hendry=E2=80=99s head explode. For one thing, that is an abuse =
of terminology: Black swans are supposed to be rare and extreme, and if you=
 are talking about =E2=80=9Cnumerous black swans=E2=80=9D then you have mad=
e errors both of language and of risk management.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, though =E2=80=A6=C2=A0I mean the whole p=
oint of the =E2=80=9Cblack swan=E2=80=9D metaphor is that if you go around =
for hundreds of years only seeing white swans, you are entitled to assume t=
hat all swans are white, and then when you travel to another continent and =
you see a black swan you are entitled to feel surprised. If you go around i=
n=C2=A0your backyard for 20 minutes only seeing gray squirrels, and then yo=
u go to your front yard and=C2=A0see a black squirrel, you will feel less s=
urprised.=C2=A0You just did not have that much data on which to form a conc=
lusion like =E2=80=9Call squirrels are gray.=E2=80=9D Hendry says to Davies=
: =E2=80=9CThe market hadn=E2=80=99t existed for more than 10 years or so. =
=E2=80=A6=C2=A0There=E2=80=99s no observation set; everything is risk.=E2=
=80=9D It is just weird to be surprised that Luna collapsed. Luna=E2=80=99s=
 existence was a blip; <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/29960075.267530/aHR0cHM6Ly9jb2lubWFya2V0Y2FwLmNvbS9jdXJyZW5jaWVzL3Rlcn=
JhdXNkLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa6e26365" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
