color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;"> doing particularly well</a> as a business. If you had the chance =
to lend money to Twitter, you might reasonably say =E2=80=9Cno thank you.=
=E2=80=9D But if you had the chance to lend money to Elon Musk, you might r=
easonably say =E2=80=9Csure he=E2=80=99s rich he=E2=80=99ll probably pay me=
 back.=E2=80=9D There are some concerns in that reasoning, maybe, but it=E2=
=80=99s more or less fine.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In any case, if you have=C2=A0<em>already=C2=
=A0</em>made the mistake of lending $13 billion to Twitter, you will defini=
tely be better off trying to change that into a loan to Musk himself. Bloom=
berg=E2=80=99s=C2=A0Davide Scigliuzzo, Sonali Basak and Paula Seligson <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29960075.267530/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTItMDgvbXVzay1iYW5rZ=
